& [MultiProgrammerRunnerDesign] is the executable design contract for future multi-Programmer execution
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [assignment_plan_support] coordination/programmer_merge_review_protocol.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T21:20:00Z

  + [design_status] is ready_for_implementation_slice
  + [authority_boundary] is runner_contract_not_parallel_execution_proof
  + [purpose] is connect ProgrammerAssignmentPlan, planned WorkSlice records, per-Programmer outputs, Manager review, Shaliach review, and merge review without writing unreviewed patches to the target workspace

  = must: execute only assignments derived from an approved code-layer package
  = must: preserve one raw output and one ProgrammerReport per assignment
  = must: write each Programmer output under a separate run-local implementation root before merge review
  = must: keep rejected, blocked, and duplicate outputs visible
  = must: require Manager review before an assignment can enter merge consideration
  = must: require Shaliach review when an assignment output changes scope, authority, lineage, data shape, artifact form, or verification evidence
  = must: produce merge-review inputs without applying merged patches to the target workspace

  - never: overwrite one Programmer output with another
  - never: treat a successful LLM response as accepted implementation
  - never: mutate the project workspace from multi-Programmer output until target patch and rollback policy exists

& [RunnerInputContract] is the required input set
  + [input] is approved code.package.sop
  + [input] is ProgrammerAssignmentPlan
  + [input] is WorkSlice for each assignment
  + [input] is configured Programmer role and model route
  + [input] is approved layer package lineage
  + [input] is merge review protocol surface

& [AssignmentLifecycle] is the state machine for one Programmer assignment
  + [state] is planned
  + [state] is executing
  + [state] is output_written
  + [state] is manager_review_pending
  + [state] is accepted_for_merge
  + [state] is rework_requested
  + [state] is rejected
  + [state] is blocked
  + [transition] is planned_to_executing when runner claims the assignment
  + [transition] is executing_to_output_written when raw output and run-local files are written
  + [transition] is output_written_to_manager_review_pending when ProgrammerReport exists
  + [transition] is manager_review_pending_to_accepted_for_merge when ManagerReview accepts output
  + [transition] is manager_review_pending_to_rework_requested when ManagerReview requests revision
  + [transition] is any_to_blocked when output violates path, authority, or required artifact form

& [RunnerOutputContract] is the artifact set created by the executable runner
  + [artifact] is multi_programmer_execution_plan.sop
  + [artifact] is <slice_id>.<programmer_name>.work_slice.sop
  + [artifact] is <slice_id>.<programmer_name>.raw.md
  + [artifact] is <slice_id>.<programmer_name>.programmer_report.sop
  + [artifact] is <slice_id>.<programmer_name>.manager_review.sop
  + [artifact] is <slice_id>.<programmer_name>.file_change_surface.sop
  + [artifact] is multi_programmer_merge_review_input.sop
  + [artifact] is merge_conflict_ledger.sop when overlap or conflict exists
  + [artifact] is multi_programmer_runner_log.jsonl

& [MergeReviewReadinessContract] is the condition for entering merge review
  + [required] is every accepted assignment has raw output, ProgrammerReport, ManagerReview, and file change surface
  + [required] is every rejected or rework assignment has visible reason and source artifact refs
  + [required] is file paths are run-local and cannot escape the assignment output root
  + [required] is overlap between accepted outputs is recorded before merge
  + [required] is merged output remains run-local until target workspace writer policy is implemented

& [ImplementationOrder] is the next safe build order
  + [step_1] is add dataclasses for assignment execution records and merge review input records
  + [step_2] is add pure functions that build runner plan and output artifact names from ProgrammerAssignmentPlan
  + [step_3] is add tests for two Programmers producing separate run-local roots
  + [step_4] is integrate runner after code package approval behind a config flag or conservative default
  + [step_5] is add Manager and Shaliach review records before any merge consideration
